## JavaScript Async Cheat Sheet

### Promise Basics
```javascript
const p = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  // async work here
  resolve(data);   // success
  reject(error);   // failure
});
p.then(data => ...).catch(err => ...);
```

### Async/Await
```javascript
async function fetchUser(id) {
  try {
    const res = await fetch(`/api/users/${id}`);
    const data = await res.json();
    return data;
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Fetch failed:', err);
  }
}
```

### Parallel Execution
```javascript
// Sequential (slower): 2 seconds total
const a = await fetchA();  // 1s
const b = await fetchB();  // 1s

// Parallel (faster): 1 second total
const [a, b] = await Promise.all([fetchA(), fetchB()]);
```

### Common Pitfalls
- Forgetting `await` → you get a Promise object, not the resolved value
- Not catching errors → unhandled Promise rejection crashes Node
- `await` in a regular (non-async) function → SyntaxError
